---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SpoonAsia — Decoding Thai F&B for International Investors"
  description="F&B investment intelligence for the Thailand market. Unit economics, neighborhood alpha, and decision frameworks for foreign operators evaluating Thailand."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-slug">
        <span>Dispatch № 047</span>
        <span class="rule"></span>
        <span>13 May 2026 · Bangkok</span>
      </div>

      <span class="hero-eyebrow">F&amp;B Investment Intelligence</span>

      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Decoding Thai F&amp;B for foreign <em>operators</em>
      </h1>

      <p class="hero-deck">
        Unit economics, neighborhood alpha, and decision frameworks for international investors, suppliers, and operators evaluating Thailand. Not pitch decks. Not broker copy. The numbers and context most market-entry reports leave out.
      </p>

      <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-num">$32<span class="unit">B</span></div>
          <div class="hero-stat-label">Thai F&amp;B Market<br>Krungsri Research 2025</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-num">68<span class="unit">%</span></div>
          <div class="hero-stat-label">Independent<br>Operator Share</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-num">7.4<span class="unit">%</span></div>
          <div class="hero-stat-label">CAGR Casual<br>Dining 2024–28</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-num">3<span class="unit">/10</span></div>
          <div class="hero-stat-label">Foreign Chains<br>Profitable Y3</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-cta-row">
        <a href="/decoded" class="btn-primary">
          <span>Read the latest Decoded</span>
          <span>→</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/watch" class="btn-secondary">Watch episode 04 →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- DECODED -->
  <section class="section" id="decoded">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div>
        <div class="section-eyebrow">— Decoded · Long-form analysis</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Reports built for <em>investment decisions</em></h2>
      </div>
      <a href="/decoded" class="section-link">All Decoded reports →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="decoded-grid">
      <article class="decoded-card featured">
        <div class="decoded-meta">
          <span class="tag">Unit Economics</span>
          <span>13 May 2026 · 18 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Why three foreign coffee chains lost money in Bangkok — and one didn't</h3>
        <p>The pitch deck shows $4.50 ticket size, 220 covers a day, 28% gross margin. The P&amp;L shows tea money, BOI compliance, GP loss on delivery, and a landlord ratchet that nobody mentioned. Strip away branding. Look at the skeleton.</p>
        <div class="stat-strip">
          <div><strong>4 chains</strong>Analysed</div>
          <div><strong>$1.2M</strong>Avg. Y1 burn</div>
          <div><strong>27 mo.</strong>To breakeven</div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="decoded-card">
        <div class="decoded-meta">
          <span class="tag">Neighborhood</span>
          <span>06 May 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Thonglor looks like Brooklyn. It behaves like Roppongi.</h3>
        <p>Foot traffic is not customer traffic. What you're really paying for in a 600 baht-per-sqm lease.</p>
        <div class="stat-strip">
          <div><strong>฿580/sqm</strong>Median rent</div>
          <div><strong>3.2×</strong>vs. Ari</div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="decoded-card">
        <div class="decoded-meta">
          <span class="tag">Market Entry</span>
          <span>29 Apr 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Master franchise or wholly-owned? The 2026 decision matrix</h3>
        <p>BOI changes shifted the math. Three structural questions to ask before committing capital.</p>
        <div class="stat-strip">
          <div><strong>4 paths</strong>Compared</div>
          <div><strong>11 risks</strong>Mapped</div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="decoded-card">
        <div class="decoded-meta">
          <span class="tag">Supply Chain</span>
          <span>22 Apr 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Why Japanese suppliers underprice for Thailand — and overlose</h3>
        <p>The distributor margin stack in Thailand has three layers most foreign manufacturers never see.</p>
        <div class="stat-strip">
          <div><strong>17–24%</strong>Hidden margin</div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="decoded-card">
        <div class="decoded-meta">
          <span class="tag">Consumer</span>
          <span>15 Apr 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Thai middle class is bigger than the deck says — and smaller than it spends</h3>
        <p>Real disposable income data, not "rising middle class" platitudes from 2018 reports.</p>
        <div class="stat-strip">
          <div><strong>23.4M</strong>Households</div>
          <div><strong>฿38k</strong>Median income</div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EPISODE -->
  <section class="episode" id="episodes">
    <div class="episode-inner">
      <div class="episode-visual">
        <span class="episode-corner tl">EP.04 · REC ●</span>
        <span class="episode-corner br">14:32</span>
        <div class="episode-play" aria-label="Play episode 4"></div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <span class="episode-tag">Episode 04 · Now Playing</span>
        <h2>The shabu math: $6 a head and 25% gross margin, explained</h2>
        <p class="episode-deck">
          A Bangkok shabu chain charges what a Singapore operator would call suicide pricing — and clears margin a Tokyo operator would envy. The variable nobody puts in slide one.
        </p>
        <ul class="episode-bullets">
          <li>Why ฿299 buffet pricing isn't the unit-economics story</li>
          <li>The hidden labor arbitrage built into Thai casual dining</li>
          <li>What happens to this model when minimum wage hits ฿450</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="episode-meta">
          <span>14 min · Long-form</span>
          <span>Segment A · Investor</span>
          <span>Program A · Unit Economics</span>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn-primary">
          <span>Watch on YouTube</span>
          <span>→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FRAMEWORK -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div>
        <div class="section-eyebrow">— How I read this market</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Two lenses, one <em>analyst</em></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="framework">
      <div class="framework-col">
        <div class="framework-num">PROGRAM A</div>
        <h3>The <em>Unit Economics</em></h3>
        <p>I look at F&amp;B brands the way a CFO does due diligence — strip away marketing narrative, founder charisma, brand glow. The skeleton either holds weight or it doesn't.</p>
        <div class="framework-quote">
          "The pitch deck shows revenue. The P&amp;L shows reality. The variance is your due-diligence question."
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="framework-col">
        <div class="framework-num">PROGRAM B</div>
        <h3>The <em>Neighborhood Alpha</em></h3>
        <p>Neighborhoods are organisms. Rent is a price tag on a specific kind of human traffic. Two locations on the same street can be running completely different businesses.</p>
        <div class="framework-quote">
          "The rent isn't for the space. It's for the access. And access is not foot traffic."
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PENGUIN X -->
  <section class="penguin-x" id="penguin-x">
    <div class="penguin-x-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="penguin-x-eyebrow">— Penguin X · Advisory</div>
        <h2>When reading isn't <em>enough</em>.</h2>
        <p>
          For operators past the research phase. Site validation in Bangkok and three secondary cities, P&amp;L stress-testing against Thai operating reality, and the conversations local partners won't have on a Zoom call.
        </p>
        <a href="/penguin-x" class="btn-dark">
          <span>Request a briefing</span>
          <span class="arrow">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <ul class="penguin-x-services">
        <li><span>Market entry brief</span><span class="price">5 days</span></li>
        <li><span>Site validation visit</span><span class="price">2 weeks</span></li>
        <li><span>Unit economics audit</span><span class="price">10 days</span></li>
        <li><span>Partner shortlist</span><span class="price">3 weeks</span></li>
        <li><span>Quarterly retainer</span><span class="price">By case</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NEWSLETTER -->
  <section class="newsletter" id="newsletter">
    <div class="newsletter-inner">
      <div class="newsletter-mono">The Weekly Dispatch</div>
      <h2>One report. Every <em>Tuesday</em>. No filler.</h2>
      <p>What I'm watching in Thai F&amp;B this week — one chart, one observation, one decision question. Read by operators in 24 countries.</p>
      <form class="newsletter-form" onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); this.querySelector('button').textContent='Sent ✓';">
        <input type="email" placeholder="you@company.com" required />
        <button type="submit">Subscribe →</button>
      </form>
      <div class="newsletter-fine">Free · 4-min read · Unsubscribe anytime</div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
